<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 94 / International Company News: Rio Algom improves
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Canadian mining group Rio Algom's metals distribution business improved in
the fourth quarter, but mining operations posted lower revenues, writes
Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
Net profit was CDollars 11.2m (USDollars 8.3m), or 25 cents a share, against
CDollars 10.1m, or 20 cents, a year earlier, on revenues of CDollars 243m,
against CDollars 241m.
The figure for all of 1993 was CDollars 33.9m, or 73 cents, against CDollars
39.4m, or 88 cents, on revenues of CDollars 955m, compared with CDollars
905m.
Mining operations are moving away from uranium to base metals.
Production has started at the Cerro Colorado project in Chile, which will
produce 90m pounds of high-quality cathode yearly.
</TEXT>
