FT  04 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Exports help Record to Pounds 2.4m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Helped by improved exports, Record Holdings achieved a jump in pre-tax
profits from Pounds 1.09m to Pounds 2.41m in 1993.
The Sheffield-based toolmaker attributed the rise to an improvement in
overall efficiency, improved prices and the absence of any large
reorganisation costs.
