FT  04 MAR 94 / International Company News: Inishtech up 11% to IPounds 8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A strong second half helped Inishtech, the Dublin-based maker of disposable
hygiene and protective packaging and self adhesive labels, lift pre-tax
profits 11 per cent to IPounds 8.1m (Pounds 7.8m) in 1993. Profits in 1992
were IPounds 7.28m.
Sales improved from IPounds 52.7m to IPounds 60.3m. After tax of IPounds
1.59m (IPounds 1.2m) and a IPounds 661,000 (IPounds 713,000) charge for
goodwill amortisation, earnings per share amounted to 35.6p (32.8p).
Adjusted earnings were 39.6p (37.1p).
At the interim stage the directors indicated they would recommend a final
dividend of 4.75p. However, in light of the improved trading conditions they
are now recommending a final of 5.5p, making a total of 8p (6.05p).
