FT  04 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Flemings to launch India fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Flemings is launching the first UK-listed investment trust concentrating on
India. It will be a single country fund, rather than covering the
sub-continent.
The launch announcement has been delayed several weeks through problems with
India's imposition of both short-term and long-term capital gains tax on
foreign investors, except through Mauritius. The problems have been
resolved.
The trust hopes to raise Pounds 100m or more, to be raised through a
placing, starting within a few weeks, and a public offer, possibly in May.
The fund will be managed from Hong Kong by Jonathan Boyer, who already
manages the Hong Kong-registered Jardine Fleming India unit trust. Research
will come from Jardine Fleming's Bombay office.
