FT  04 MAR 94 / Observer: Party line
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A bit odd that Midland Independent Newspapers, which is being floated on the
stock market, has the same chairman as the Tory party. Sir Norman Fowler can
point to the fact that he accepted the chairmanship of the regional
newspaper chain a good six months before he was tapped to be party chairman.
