<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 94 / Disqualification for 17 directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A total of 17 company directors were disqualified for up to 12 years during
the final quarter of 1993, Department of Trade and Industry figures showed
yesterday. Eight disqualifications arose from civil proceedings after
confidential company investigations, and nine resulted from criminal
proceedings following reports from Official Receivers.
The DTI's investigations division dealt with 260 requests for investigations
in the quarter, bringing the number for the year ending December 31 1993 to
1,086, an increase of 12 per cent on the previous year's 967. Of 260
requests, the division accepted 98 for confidential investigations.
