FT  04 MAR 94 / Brown attends cabinet discussion at Downing Street
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK entrepreneur David Brown (right), who has played a key role in the
development of export markets for Proton, Malaysia's national car, is seen
leaving Downing Street yesterday after cabinet discussions certain to have
centred on the breach in trade relations between the UK and Malaysia.
Mr Brown was not available for comment on the talks. However, he is known to
have maintained close and cordial contacts with key Malaysian government
figures since the late 1980s, when he founded Proton Cars (UK).
The UK has become an important market for Proton - with sales providing
Malaysia with annual earnings approaching Pounds 100m.
Businessmen such as Mr Brown, who has a permanent office in Kuala Lumpur,
could provide a sounding board and possible link between the two sides in
the dispute.
Mr Brown is currently preparing the ground for the launch of Proton exports
to continental Europe.
