Baroness Chalker, minister for overseas development, yesterday said that she
had opposed government funding of the Malaysian Pergau dam project on
economic grounds.
She also told the Commons foreign affairs committee that it was unusual for
the cost of a project to rise by as much as the Pergau dam had in such a
short time.
Under persistent questioning over the alleged link between the aid for the
dam and a Pounds 1bn arms deal, she conceded that it might be more accurate
