<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 94 / Sales of books rise by up to 10%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The number of books sold has increased by between 5 per cent and 10 per cent
over the past 18 months, a survey by Book Marketing, the book industry
research group, has found.
About 300m books are sold each year with more than a third of all buyers
purchasing at least 16 books a year. Over the past five years puzzle and
quiz books have overtaken romantic fiction as the largest category of books
sold.
