<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 94 / Company start-ups increase sharply
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A sharp rise in company formations last month has been reported by Jordans,
the Bristol-based information company, Philip Coggan writes.
It said 10,498 companies were formed in February, a 6.8 per cent increase on
the same month last year. January saw a 4.8 per cent increase. The
information is compiled using data supplied by Companies House and excludes
Northern Ireland.
Excluding March, which is a big month for company formations because it is
the end of the financial year, last month's figure was the largest since May
1991.
Last year 113,561 new companies were formed compared with 107,375 in 1992.
</TEXT>
