FT  03 MAR 94 / International Company News: Swire increases Coke interests
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE LUCAS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Swire Pacific, the Hong Kong-based property, aviation and trading group, has
raised its stake in its bottling joint ventures with Coca-Cola and plans to
invest HKDollars 1bn (USDollars 129m) in bottling plants in China, writes
Louise Lucas in Hong Kong.
Swire will lift its share of Coca-Cola Swire Beverages to 87.5 per cent from
50 per cent. The joint venture will change its name to Swire Beverages, and
Coca-Cola will hold the remaining interest.
The company will also take an additional 2 per cent of Swire Bottlers and 19
per cent of BC Development, the holding company for the Coca-Cola bottling
interests in three China provinces, and 29 per cent of the Taiwan Coca-Cola
Bottling Company from Swire Beverages.
Coca-Cola will invest the USDollars 18.5m from the sale to develop new
operations in the region.
