<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 94 / International Company News: Rio Algom improves for quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Canadian mining group Rio Algom's metals distribution business improved in
the fourth quarter, but mining operations posted lower revenue, writes
Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
Net profit was CDollars 11.2m (USDollars 8.3m), or 25 cents a share, against
CDollars 10.1m, or 20 cents, a year earlier, on revenues of CDollars 243m
against CDollars 241m. The figure for 1993 was CDollars 33.9m, or 73 cents,
against CDollars 39.4m, or 88 cents, on revenues of CDollars 955m against
CDollars 905m.
Mining operations are moving away from uranium to base metals. Production
has started at the Cerro Colorado project in Chile, which will produce 90m
pounds of high-quality cathode yearly.
</TEXT>
