<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 94 / International Company News: Court rejects Blockbuster
investor move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A Delaware court has rejected a move to block a Dollars 1.25bn investment by
Blockbuster Entertainment, the US home video company, in cable television
group Viacom.
The application had been brought by some shareholders in Blockbuster, which
had agreed to pay Dollars 55 a share for a stake in Viacom to provide cash
for the cable-TV company's winning bid for Paramount Communications.
Viacom's non-voting 'B' shares were trading at around Dollars 29 this week.
The Delaware chancery court said blocking the investment would cause
'enormous uncertainty with widespread repercussions, causing Paramount
Communication's stockholders to reconsider their decision to tender their
shares under Viacom's tender offer'.
Blockbuster shareholders have yet to vote on whether to accept an all-share
offer for the company from Viacom.
Although it has already received the backing of Blockbuster's board, the
deal has come under fire from some shareholders.
</TEXT>
