FT  03 MAR 94 / UK Company News: EFM aims to double Small Cos Trust's size
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Edinburgh Fund Managers' Small Companies Investment Trust is aiming to
almost double in size with a conversion share issue.
The trust - launched last August - invests in UK quoted companies mainly
capitalised at under Pounds 100m. It has net assets of Pounds 58m.
The maximum size of the C share issue has been set at Pounds 50m, after the
placing drew irrevocable undertakings for Pounds 20m-worth of C shares at
100p.
The public offer opens today and closes on March 23. Warrants will be
attached on a 1-for-5 basis. Conversion will take place by September 30.
The Foreign &amp; Colonial Income Growth investment trust, the group's first
investment trust to concentrate on the UK, has raised Pounds 7m from a
placing. The public offer, which closes on March 25, has been given a Pounds
250m limit, to avoid any need to scale back applications.
