<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Perkins completes debt restructuring
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Perkins Foods has completed the restructuring of its debt profile with a
Pounds 30m multi-currency revolving credit facility. This follows a Pounds
32m, 10 year private placement arranged in the US last December.
Mr Ian Blackburn, finance director, said the new facility, which lasts for
four years and can be drawn in any European currency, would cover the
possible redemption of the group's D-mark convertible bonds. It gives the
group a more structured debt profile, he said.
Both the private placement and new facility have covenants that take account
of the substantial goodwill write-offs the group has taken because of its
acquisitive past. A large part of the Pounds 150m of goodwill written off is
treated in the covenants as an asset.
The facility was arranged by Barclays Bank and the other banks involved are
Nationale Investeringsbank, ABN Amro Bank and Berliner Handels-und
Franfurter Bank.
</TEXT>
