<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Pizzaland Scottish growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BrightReasons, the private company which owns the Pizzaland restaurant
chain, yesterday announced an expansion plan which could pave the way for a
flotation.
The group, which operates 160 pizza and pasta restaurants around the UK,
said it was acquiring a further six outlets in Scotland and one in England
for an undisclosed sum.
Mr Michael Guthrie, group chairman, said the acquisition from
Edinburgh-based Pizza Gallery had been funded by loans from Samuel Montagu,
Bank of Scotland and Banque Indosuez.
Mr Guthrie, a former chairman and chief executive of Mecca Leisure, said
yesterday: 'We are now considering a float, but it's not imminent.'
The group was committed to further expansion, and intended to spend up to
Pounds 4m developing operations in Scotland, where it now has 22 outlets.
</TEXT>
