FT  03 MAR 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The BBC continues to dominate the younger sector of the comedy market. From
today their three-deep Thursday night line-up begins with Dawn French in a
new series of Murder Most Horrid (9.00 BBC2). I was not the greatest fan of
the first series, though French can be very funny. That is followed by
Absolutely Fabulous written by her partner, Jennifer Saunders, who also
stars as the awful fashion PRO, Edina (9.30 BBC1). Then comes Ben Elton with
his frenetic stand-up routine in The Man From Auntie (10.00 BBC1).
In preparation for a new series about one of television's most memorable
characters, steeplejack Fred Dibnah, BBC2 repeats the 1987 programme A Year
With Fred (8.00).
Channel 4 screens the second episode of Phil Agland's series about life in a
Chinese city, Beyond The clouds (9.00) and then begins a serial adaptation
of Joanna Trollope's best selling novel The Rector's Wife. Lindsay Duncan
plays the title role in a story which is like a cross between a novel by the
author's namesake and ancestor, Anthony Trollope, and 'The Archers' (10.00).
